       fhir:comment [ fhir:v "For rest-hook, and websocket, the end-point must be an http: or https: URL; for email, a mailto: url, for sms, a tel: url, and for message the endpoint can be in any form of url the server understands (usually, http: or mllp:). The URI is allowed to be relative; in which case, it is relative to the server end-point (since their may be more than one, clients should avoid using relative URIs)\n\nThis address will be to the service base, without any parameters, or sub-services or resources tacked on.\n\nE.g. for a WADO-RS endpoint, the url should be \"https://pacs.hospital.org/wado-rs\"\n\nand not \"https://pacs.hospital.org/wado-rs/studies/1.2.250.1.59.40211.12345678.678910/series/1.2.250.1.59.40211.789001276.14556172.67789/instances/...\"." ] ;
